            , to weave: on his bringing it home, on the 30th of May, there was wanting one pound two ounces and a half: the prisoner was suspected, and Cosins took her up; and upon being charged with taking it, she owned, in my hearing, at the alehouse, and before the Justices in Whitechapel, and at Hick's-Hall, that she had taken seven ounces, and sold about five or six ounces to one 
               <persName id="t17640607-10-person118">
                  Anne 
